Using log base 10 function - O(1) Time and O(1) Space
- We can use log10(logarithm of base 10) to count the number of digits of positive numbers (logarithm is not defined for negative numbers). 
- For negative numbers, first take the absolute value of n, since logarithm is not defined for negative values.
- Digit count of n = floor(log10(n) + 1) 

public class GfG {
    public static int countDigit(int n) {
        // Handle zero separately
        if (n == 0) return 1;

        // Convert negative to positive
        n = Math.abs(n);

        return (int)Math.floor(Math.log10(n)) + 1;
    }
}
