Converting Number to String - O(Number of digits) Time and O(Number of digits) Space
- We can convert the number into a string and then find the length of the string to get the number of digits in the original number. 
- If the number is negative, the string will contain a '-' sign, so subtract 1 from the length.

public class GfG {
    public static int countDigit(int n) {
        // Convert integer to string
        String num = Integer.toString(n);

        // If negative, exclude '-' sign
        if (num.charAt(0) == '-')
            return num.length() - 1;

        return num.length();
    }
}
